    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<code>null</code> is somewhat special in Java, in that it&#39;s exempt from type checking.  Otherwise you would not be able to, eg, <code>return null;</code> from a method that returns a <code>Hippopotamus</code>, if you happen to be fresh out of hippopotami."
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1899638,
      "reputation" : 1746,
