      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@fvrghl: Like much of Java&#39;s exception handling, there is no <i>valid</i> reason to <code>throw null</code>, but it might come up in a buggy program. Having well defined semantics for buggy constructs can simplify the debugging of and minimise the security consequences of the bug."
