      "body" : "@bharal: It might not be possible to know at compile time. In the exact case of <code>throw null</code>, it is, but in a more general case where the exception object is decided upon at runtime, there may be no way to know. Evidently the addition (to the JLS) of a special case for <code>null</code> literals was not seen as worthwhile, since it is a very easy mistake to avoid anyway."
