      "body" : "@fvrghl Remember that you can&#39;t just <code>throw new SomethingException()</code> but also <code>throw existingExceptionYouGotFromSomewhere</code>. You would do that when you have a complex exception handler which is able to process some exceptions itself but propagates others to an upper layer. In this case, the exception handling code which re-throws an exception might have a bug which causes the exception object to be <code>null</code>."
