    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>It looks like it's not that <code>null</code> is treated as a <code>NullPointerException</code>, but that the act of attempting to <code>throw null</code> <em>itself</em> throws a <code>NullPointerException</code>.  </p>\n\n<p>In other words, <code>throw</code> checks that its argument is nonnull, and if it is null, it throws a <code>NullPointerException</code>.</p>\n\n<p>JLS 14.18 <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se7/html/jls-14.html#jls-14.18\">specifies</a> this behavior:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>If evaluation of the Expression completes normally, producing a null value, then an instance V' of class NullPointerException is created and thrown instead of null. The throw statement then completes abruptly, the reason being a throw with value V'.</p>\n</blockquote>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2871026,
      "reputation" : 31779,
      "user_id" : 2464386,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 84,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/508c3cc96cdca194c0204f1f7c2758e0?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "ajb",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2464386/ajb"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 14,
    "last_activity_date" : 1373476710,
    "creation_date" : 1373476710,
    "answer_id" : 17576962,
    "question_id" : 17576922,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Don't know for sure, but I'm guessing that \"throw null\"; does <em>not</em> work, and trying it causes the program to throw an exception, and that exception happens to be (drum roll) NullPointerException...</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 440158,
      "reputation" : 330010,
      "user_id" : 829571,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 94,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/zflGZ.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "assylias",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/829571/assylias"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 21,
    "last_activity_date" : 1373476976,
    "creation_date" : 1373476976,
    "answer_id" : 17577027,
    "question_id" : 17576922,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>It behaves in compliance with the <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se7/html/jls-14.html#jls-14.18\">JLS</a>:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>If evaluation of the Expression completes normally, producing a null value, then an instance V' of class NullPointerException is created and thrown instead of null. </p>\n</blockquote>\n"
  }, {
