    "creation_date" : 1373641949,
    "answer_id" : 17618214,
    "question_id" : 17576922,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><em>null</em> can be cast to anything*, including an Exception. Just as you could return null if your method signature specifies you should return an Exception (or indeed a string, or Person class), you can throw it.</p>\n\n<p>*Excluding primitive types.</p>\n"
